I lovED this place until today. I always tip, ALWAYS. In order for me to tip you though, YOU HAVE TO GIVE PEOPLE THEIR CHANGE BACK FIRST. Apparently the new delivery guy doesn’t know that and think your change is his. Then he thinks it’s okay to get snappy and tell customers “don’t call Bedford Pizza anymore,” well guess what? I WON’T and you can take this lashing out that you asked for with you.  Then I call to tell them how their staff is acting and he says “I’m sorry about that BUT WHATEVER, they work for tips.” People like that are gonna try the wrong person one day and someone isn’t gonna have as much restraint as me and Bedford Pizza is gonna be looking for another delivery person.

The pizza here is great, exactly as you'd expect from this area. I'd say the cheese really shines - he'd told me he gets it fresh from Arthur Ave often, and it really shows. The sauce and the cheese really blend well.  The thing that really shines here is the service. The man behind the counter is always friendly, and if there's slack time, he'll strike up a conversation now and then. The guy really makes ordering there a joy every time. Even always throws in a few garlic knots with each pizza, too.  Shows you the pizza every time before closing it, just to make sure it's fine and also to put on toppings. Then before letting you go, he always asks if you need free paper plates or napkins to go with the pizza. I never need it, but the gesture is always appreciated. Recently became my go-to place for pizza, though other places in the area are great in their own way.

I live in Queens. I came to visit family in the Bronx. I ordered from here because it was the closest to where I was.  The order was wrong. Wrong toppings....I guess we all make mistakes. :/  Pizza was cut up really sloppy.  Just looked so gross like it was thrown like a football. No joke.  It had four garlic knots on each corner of the box with the pizza.  More like garlic Rocks.  I think if Gordon Ramsey saw the pizza. He would cry. But whatever. I ate the wrong pizza. Didn't want to wait....family was too hungry.  I called them and the guy was nice but he said he would cook the extra toppings and bring it over.  Lol.  That's so weird.  I didn't want to wait and ask for another pizza.  Family was too hungry.  Will NOT order from here again.  "My Place pizza" is where I grew up eating real pizza.  Should have ordered from them.  But the guy on the phone and the delivery guy was more professional than another other delivery guy. All three stars are to them.
